Dana Air has taken delivery of some of its aircraft from maintenance as part of efforts to beef up operations. Daily Trust reports that the airline recently halted its scheduled flights following the delay in the arrival of its aircraft from maintenance. Daily Trust reports that the airline had however reinstated scheduled flights after taking delivery of no fewer than two aircraft from maintenance. The airline yesterday confirmed that it has received some of the aircraft from maintenance and will be introducing a flash sale of N45,000 for those who plan their trips early enough and book ahead on its website. Head, Corporate Communications of the airline, Kingsley Ezenwa said, “We are pleased to announce that we have taken delivery of some of our aircraft from maintenance. “These aircraft have undergone proper maintenance in line with our strict safety standards, documentation and certification to be released for our scheduled flights.”